\begin_layout Section
Diagram
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "froh92"

\end_inset

 developed a ternary diagram to represent focal mechanisms based in the
 trigonometrical relation: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\sin^{2}\iota_{T}+\sin^{2}\iota_{B}+\sin^{2}\iota_{P}=1,
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\iota_{T}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\iota_{B}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\iota_{P}$
\end_inset

 are the plunges of the axis T, B and P of the SMT.
 This relation is true for three orthogonal axes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As the equation of a sphere with radius unity is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2}=1
\end{equation}

\end_inset

and all the plunge angles are positive between 0°and 90°, then the representatio
n of a focal mechanism defined by these axes is equivalent to the projection
 of a point in an spherical octant over a planar surface.
 As a sphere is not a developable surface can not be projected onto a plane
 without distortion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The projection used by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "froh92"

\end_inset

 represents this spherical octant as a triangle, which is equivalent to
 the gnomonic geographical projection.
 In this projection we define the angles 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\psi=\arctan\left(\dfrac{\sin\iota_{T}}{\sin\iota_{P}}\right)-45^{\circ},
\end{equation}

\end_inset

and 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\iota_{s}=\arcsin\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{3}}=\arctan\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{2}}\approx35.26^{\circ},
\end{equation}

\end_inset

which is the angle of the ternary symmetry axis with the orthogonal axes
 of the octant.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From these angles the 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 coordinates over the plane are given by: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
x=\dfrac{\cos\iota_{B}\cdot\sin\psi}{\sin\iota_{s}\cdot\sin\iota_{B}+\cos\iota_{s}\cdot\sin\iota_{B}\cdot\cos\psi}\\
y=\dfrac{\cos\iota_{s}\cdot\sin\iota_{B}-\sin\iota_{s}\cdot\cos\iota_{B}\cdot\cos\psi}{\sin\iota_{s}\cdot\sin\iota_{B}+\cos\iota_{s}\cdot\sin\iota_{B}\cdot\cos\psi}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

The angle 
\begin_inset Formula $\iota_{s}$
\end_inset

 in the projection is the angle of the plunges of the axes T, B and P for
 the focal mechanism that occupies the barycentre of the ternary diagram
 where 
\begin_inset Formula $x=y=0$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

